<p>Given a string "a b c d", I'd like to return substrings in the following format: </p>  <p>"a b",  "b c",  "c d"</p>  <p>I'm having a bit of trouble wrapping my mind around this concept in the most efficient way possible in time it takes to complete.</p>  <p>Code format:</p>  <pre><code>NSString *sentence = @"Hello I am a string"; </code></pre>  <p>I want this to return the following:</p>  <p>"Hello I", "I am", "am a", "a string"</p>